WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.720
Hello and welcome back. In this lesson, we will use codex to add an open router free model to

00:00:06.720 --> 00:00:29.460
OpenClaw. Sign into open router. Let's create a new key. We will call it test. I will delete

00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:43.550
this key after shooting this video. Copy this key and save it in notepad. Go to the models page.

00:00:45.810 --> 00:00:52.530
In the search box, type in free and it will list down all the free models you can use.

00:00:53.330 --> 00:00:58.460
Let's scroll through and take a look. There are many good ones.

00:01:00.620 --> 00:01:04.460
You should choose those with instruct and tool calling capabilities.

00:01:05.740 --> 00:01:32.980
If it has vision, that would also be useful. Note that uncensored models are also available.

00:01:32.980 --> 00:01:37.620
These models will not refuse to do something because of ethical reasons.

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:43.780
We will try nvidia's nemotron 3 super but you can try anything else you prefer

00:01:45.620 --> 00:02:00.830
click on the nemotron link and copy its official name then paste it into notepad

00:02:02.670 --> 00:02:11.580
Next we launch codex. We then tell codex we want to add a new open router model

00:02:11.580 --> 00:02:20.050
and make it the default, but we still want to keep the other models intact.

00:02:23.410 --> 00:02:33.520
We paste in the official name for Nemotron, and also paste in your open router API key.

00:02:47.550 --> 00:02:53.150
We also ask it to make backup copies of the configuration files before making any changes.

00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:07.920
Also, remember to give it full access to your PC.

00:03:09.970 --> 00:03:20.480
And Codex goes to work. Occasionally, it will ask you to approve certain actions.

00:03:20.480 --> 00:03:36.210
just click on yes and don't ask again for that action. I then add additional instructions asking

00:03:36.210 --> 00:03:54.370
it to remove all old API keys for open router and update them with the one I provided. I then click

00:03:54.370 --> 00:03:59.650
on the steer button so that it can be read by codex without interrupting what it is currently

00:03:59.650 --> 00:04:10.160
doing. Continue to approve every action that it asks you permission for. Then I added further

00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:15.040
instructions asking it to also update any environment variables that stores

00:04:15.040 --> 00:04:26.220
the open router API key. Again, I click on the steer button. I will speed up the

00:04:26.220 --> 00:04:52.140
video. After making the changes, Codex restarts the OpenClaw gateway. It then

00:04:52.140 --> 00:05:03.860
gives a report of what it has done. Let's open Telegram. Delete the chat history

00:05:03.860 --> 00:05:21.270
and start a new session. Open CLAW replies and I ask it what model are you

00:05:21.270 --> 00:05:29.900
on. It replies that it is on Nemotron 3 Free. It works.

00:05:29.900 --> 00:05:39.940
I type in further messages just to confirm and again it replies. So Codex

00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:57.930
has successfully added a new model to Open CLAW. Let's head back to Codex and

00:05:57.930 --> 00:06:03.490
and ask it to save this workflow to memory so that in future when we ask it to add another

00:06:03.490 --> 00:06:09.150
model it will remember how to.

00:06:09.150 --> 00:06:14.070
It successfully saved it to memory and then informs us.

00:06:14.070 --> 00:06:22.540
I ask it where did it save to and it tells me the file names and the path to those files

00:06:22.540 --> 00:06:26.580
as well.

00:06:26.580 --> 00:06:30.720
Let's go back to the free models list.

00:06:30.720 --> 00:06:36.350
You could try all these free models and see which ones you like.

00:06:36.350 --> 00:06:41.510
And the good news is that you don't have to pay anything for them.

00:06:41.510 --> 00:06:46.890
You could ask Codex to set up fallbacks in case one model is rate limited, it can automatically

00:06:46.890 --> 00:06:50.950
fall back into other backup models.

00:06:50.950 --> 00:06:54.970
And Codex can easily set it up for you.

00:06:54.970 --> 00:07:00.310
Just copy the official model names you want to use as fallbacks and give them to Codex

00:07:00.310 --> 00:07:02.910
to wire things up.

00:07:02.910 --> 00:07:09.410
So you can see how much easier life can be if you ask Codex to fix things for you instead

00:07:09.410 --> 00:07:14.890
of manually editing configuration files.

00:07:14.890 --> 00:07:21.490
Apart from Codex, you can also use Claude code if you have a subscription with Claude.

00:07:21.490 --> 00:07:26.810
Just a basic Claude Pro plan subscription gives you access to Claude code.

00:07:26.810 --> 00:07:30.670
It can also do everything that OpenAI Codex can do.

00:07:30.670 --> 00:07:35.030
These two are among the best AI models for agentic workflows.

00:07:35.030 --> 00:07:38.570
Both of them can fix any open-claw problems.

00:07:38.570 --> 00:07:44.390
Now, if open-claw does not work, or if you have any issues at all, just ask Codex or

00:07:44.390 --> 00:07:47.590
Claude Code to troubleshoot and fix them for you.

00:07:47.590 --> 00:07:53.110
For the Claude Code setup, download the Claude Desktop app and then on the top left, select

00:07:53.110 --> 00:07:57.670
Code, then give it full access to your machine.

00:07:57.670 --> 00:08:01.490
It works just like Codex.

00:08:01.490 --> 00:08:04.470
Let us now take a snapshot of our virtual machine.

00:08:04.470 --> 00:08:11.600
First, we shut down our Windows 11 virtual machine.

00:08:11.600 --> 00:08:16.240
Click on the take icon and give a name for this snapshot.

00:08:16.240 --> 00:08:26.500
I will call it Nemotron. Note that you can also delete older snapshots

00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:32.980
in order to free up disk storage space. For example, I will delete my oldest

00:08:32.980 --> 00:08:37.220
snapshot. Note that you don't have to choose the

00:08:37.220 --> 00:08:40.580
oldest snapshot. You may choose any snapshot to

00:08:40.580 --> 00:08:47.140
delete. The Virtual Box Manager will then merge the existing snapshots seamlessly.

00:08:47.140 --> 00:08:52.900
That's all for this video. Thanks for watching.

